Overview

Hello! I am an applied statistician that has worked in a variety of fields including education, business, and health. My PhD is in Educational Statistics and Research Methods and I also have a Masters in Industrial/Organizational Psychology, a Bachelor of Science in Psychology with a minor in business. I am happiest when working with data from a variety of fields and enjoy not just the analysis but also coding reports and graphic visualizations. I am currently working as a biostatistical analyst which involves helping professors with their research and analyzing educational outcomes. My favorite program to use for analysis and data visualization is R Statistics. My hobbies and interests include video games, music, and reading. You can follow the links above to look at a more detailed resume or look at some example projects I have coded.
